HEADWORD: Scobs
<hw>Scobs</hw>, <pos>n. sing. & pl.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>scobs</ets>, or
<ets>scobis</ets>, fr. <ets>scabere</ets> to scrape.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Raspings of ivory, hartshorn, metals, or other hard
substance.</def> <rj><au>Chambers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The dross of metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

